-- BP May Approve Disposal of $14.5 Billion in Assets, Mail on Sunday Reports
-- Tim Barwell
-- 2010-07-18T11:24:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/bp-may-approve-disposal-of-14-5-billion-in-assets-mail-on-sunday-reports.html

          
          
             BP Plc  will probably approve the
sale of assets valued at 9.5 billion pounds ($14.5 billion) at a
board meeting on July 22, the  Mail on Sunday  reported, without
saying where it got the information.  
 BP may sell assets in Argentina, where it owns 60 percent
of Pan American Energy LLC, with the stake valued at 3.5 billion
pounds, the newspaper said. Oil and gas fields valued at 1
billion pounds in Vietnam, Colombia and Venezuela may also be
sold, along with Alaskan assets valued at 5 billion pounds, it
reported.  
